author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: Script generates a committed contracts snapshot; CI compares and fails on diff; explicit update command regenerates; CHANGELOG entry required when snapshot changes.
value: "pm contracts --full JSON is the primary machine-readable surface for agents/SDK consumers; tested behaviorally but not as a whole-output snapshot, so a structural change could ship silently."
parent: pm-5k4v
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-05T15:22:04.129Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation update: added scripts/contracts-snapshot.mjs with --update/--check, committed tests/fixtures/contracts/full.json from pm contracts --full --json, exposed pnpm contracts:update/check, wired CI static gate to pnpm contracts:check, and documented the workflow in docs/TESTING.md. Evidence so far: pnpm build && pnpm contracts:update && pnpm contracts:check passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/contracts-command.spec.ts passed (19 tests). Note: an earlier parallel contracts:check raced with another command rebuilding dist; reran snapshot serially to compare against one built artifact."
  "2026-06-05T15:28:42.249Z",maintainer-agent,"Verification evidence: contracts snapshot gate remains current after changelog regeneration and full coverage. Commands passed: pnpm contracts:check; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (139 files, 2314 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines); pnpm typecheck; pnpm quality:static; pnpm security:scan; pnpm audit --audit-level low; manual temp-project smoke verified contracts schema_version=4.0.2 and 75 actions. Status: implementation is ready for PR inclusion but item remains open because this run intentionally did not commit/push."
